The paper deals with Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel attention mechanism that considers both object-level and grid-level features, which falls under the scope of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses multi-modal information and tensor decomposition, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, since the paper deals with visual data, it could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
